  "time_ut": 1662380836,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bb2\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bbf \u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bae\u0bcd  \u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 QR",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "QR for welfare grant recipients",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "P. Vijayaratne, chairman of the Welfare Benefits Council, said that the government has decided to introduce the QR code system for people eligible for welfare grants.",
        "He said the above while participating in the press conference held today (05).",
        "The scheme will target individuals who are currently receiving benefits under welfare schemes like Samurthi, Old Age Pension, Disabled Persons, Kidney Disease Assistance, etc.",
        "He also mentioned that the scheme is also targeted at people on the waiting list for subsidies and people affected by the current economic crisis.",
        "The chairman of the council informed that it is estimated that around 3.9 million families will apply for this scheme and said that this scheme will be implemented under 06 initial phases."
      ],
